title: Badgers hockey notches another tie vs. Northern Michigan
text:
Badgers hockey notches another tie vs. Northern Michigan FOX Sports Wisconsin 
Oct 11, 2015 at 12:18a ET + Updated Oct 11, 2015 at 12:33a ET 
The Wisconsin men's hockey squad used a furious rally to post a 3-all tie against Northern Michigan on Saturday night. 
Wisconsin overcame a three-goal, third-period deficit against NMU, scoring three goals in a span of 2 minutes, 49 seconds to forge the deadlock. 
Goals by Ryan Wagner, Jedd Soleway and Luke Kunin proved key for Wisconsin (0-0-2), as the Badgers posted their second tie in as many nights against Northern Michigan (0-0-2). 
The three-goal comeback was Wisconsin's first since Nov. 1, 2013 against Lake Superior State at the Kohl Center. That night, the Badgers trailed 3-0 in the first period before recovering for a 3-all tie. 
Freshman goaltender Matt Jurusik made 22 saves in his collegiate debut to post the tie. Wisconsin led, 44-25, in shots.
